programme.desc: Shirley Temple sings, dances and dispenses charm from Shanghai to the U.S. as a waif who falls asleep in a playboy's car that winds up on a cruise ship headed for the States. After being discovered at sea, she plays Cupid for the playboy and the fellow passenger he falls for.

programme.desc: A sibling dance team is booked to play London at the time of Queen Elizabeth II's marriage. The musical is famous for a pair of Fred Astaire solos, one a duet with a coat rack, the other a tap dance across a ceiling.

programme.title: Summer Stock (1950)
programme.desc: Judy Garland and Gene Kelly team in this tuneful tale about a theatrical company that stages a summer production on a financially burdened New England farm, and the down-on-her-luck owner ends up becoming the leading lady of the show.

programme.title: Girl Crazy (1943)

programme.title: Easter Parade (1948)
programme.desc: A hoofer tries to mold a singer into a sophisticated dancer in this romp.
